comments: Adams (MEM) and Nurkic (POR) mutually engage and disengage during the rebound attempt.
Johnson (POR) is moving laterally when body contact occurs with Bane (MEM), which affects his driving shot attempt.
Adams (MEM) clamps and pulls Nurkic's (POR) arm and affects his ability to rebound.
Morant (MEM) makes marginal contact with Grant (POR) at the end of his drive.
Grant (POR) gathers the ball on his right foot, takes his first step with his left, and legally lands in a jump stop before jumping with both feet on his shot attempt.
Bane (MEM) is in the lane for longer than three seconds.
Johnson (POR) moves alongside Morant's (MEM) path and is in a legal guarding position when he absorbs the incidental contact during the drive.
Morant (MEM) establishes his right foot as his pivot foot. As Morant steps through the defense, he releases the ball prior to his pivot foot returning to the floor.
Adams (MEM) establishes himself in Grant's (POR) path and absorbs the body contact during the pick.
Nurkic (POR) is moving laterally into Bane's (MEM) path when body contact occurs on the drive.
Bane (MEM) moves alongside Hart's (POR) path and marginal contact occurs at the end of his drive.
Hart (POR) commits a take foul on Bane (MEM).
Aldama (MEM) makes contact with Grant's (POR) palm/wrist during his release on his jump shot attempt.
Hart (POR) commits a take foul on Bane (MEM).
Brooks (MEM) avoids making contact with Grant (POR) during his shot attempt.
Aldama (MEM) and Eubanks (POR) both engage and separate during the rebound.
Hart (POR) commits a take foul on Bane (MEM). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
